            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="494" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–2348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-23">November 23,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received November 23—3:49 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>484. Local press today reports voluntary withdrawal yesterday Nationalist Forces
                    from Paoting. Communist north Shensi radio last night announced occupation that
                    point by Communist forces same day.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 484, repeated Nanking 714, and Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
